The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, May 6: i-flex Solutions Ltd today posted an increase of 62.70 per cent in net profit at Rs 121.70 crore for the quarter ended March 31, compared with Rs 74.80 crore for the same quarter last year. The revenues of the company increased 37.43 per cent to Rs 372.30 crore for the fourth quarter of 2005-06 from Rs 270.90 crore in the year-ago period. For the year ended March 31, the company has posted a net profit of Rs 240.70 crore compared with Rs 197.70 crore a year ago. Revenue has increased to Rs 1,153.80 crore for 2005-06 from Rs 902.90 crore in 2004-05.

 New Delhi, May 6: International Travel House (ITH) has reported a 52.83 per cent year-on-year increase in net profit at Rs 7 crore for the fiscal 2005-06. The turnover of the company during the fiscal rose 22.3 per cent to Rs 490.33 crore from Rs 400.85 crore in 2004-05. The ISO 9001 certified travel company is also strengthening its inbound division with destination management services like short excursions, guides, hotels and transport facility. During 2005-06, the company opened two additional offices each in Mumbai and Bangalore and one in Gurgaon.




